<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 13 at 9:29PM EDT  by NWS Cleveland</headline>
<description>...A line of snow showers will affect Portage...western Mahoning...
Richland...Huron...southern Medina...Ashland...Stark...southern
Summit...Wayne and southwestern Lorain Counties Until 1030 PM EDT....
At 927 PM EDT, radar indicated snow showers along a line extending
from near Newton Falls to near Doylestown to 6 miles north of
Willard, moving southeast at 15 mph.
HAZARDS INCLUDE...
Visibility dropping to less than three quarters of a mile...
Up to 2 inches of quick snow accumulation...
Locations impacted include...
Akron, Canton, Mansfield, Medina, Wooster, Ashland, Norwalk, Salem,
Ravenna, Cuyahoga Falls, Massillon, Kent, Barberton, Green, Alliance,
Wadsworth, Tallmadge, North Canton, Shelby and Louisville.
Use extra caution if you must travel. Rapid changes in visibility and
potentially slick roads may lead to accidents.</description>
